post_text:
Remember to come out for the Latrobe Spring Festival and Chili Palooza this Friday starting at 5PM! We have a lot of great entries for the chili cook off contest!

There will be a six piece band, potato sack races, three legged races, face painting, chili, hot dogs, beverages (adult and kid) and lots of fun for the whole family!

We will also announce winners for the Raffle Prize Drawing (need not be present to win and tickets will be available at the event for a limited time). We will also display and announce the winners of the coloring contest for our Jedi Chili Bean (May the 4th Be With You)!

To top it off, we are expecting beautiful weather on Friday!

All proceeds benefit the Latrobe PTC in support of the students in the Latrobe School District. We hope to see you there!

post_text:
The Latrobe PTC is looking for donations for our last big fundraiser of the year!! We have our Spring Festival and Chili Cookoff on Friday, May 4th!! As part of this event, we will hold our Spring Raffle with tickets going home with students soon.

We are looking for any donations for the raffle drawing that will be held. If you or someone you know has a business and want to donate a gift card, prize, or service in the business name, it would be greatly appreciated.

If you personally want to donate a craft, gift card, prize, etc, please reach out to us and let us know. In the past we have had gift cards, handmade quilts, photography sessions, etc donated. I know there are some talented parents out there!

Our donation coordinator is also hard at work gathering donations from local businesses.

All funds raised go back to our students! We appreciate your support!

post_text:
Whoo's Reading has until the end of the month...one week left! The two classes in the lead for fundraising and minutes read, remain in the lead!!

Ms. Olney's 6th Grade Class has read 16,410 minutes!! If you do the math, that is 273.5 hours, which equates to reading for 11.4 days straight!!!

Mr. Resha's 3rd Grade Class has done an amazing job at fundraising and reading! The 3rd graders have read 10,280 minutes...which equates to 171.3 hours or 7.13 days of straight reading. On top of all this great reading, they have some great sales strategies in this class. They have pledged so far $1,408 to the school!!! About 45% of the funds raised have come from this class alone. Good job 3rd Grade!

We still have a week to go, so results are not final. The 8th Graders are only 351 minutes behind the 3rd Graders. No pressure 8th Graders!!

So proud of all of the students for challenging themselves on their reading skills!!!

https://fund.whooosreading.org/school_orgs/latrobe-and-miller-s-hill

post_text:
Who can resist pancakes?!? From 8:00 - 11:00 they are serving up pancakes at the Odd Fellows Lodge Hall this Sunday, August 27th (next to Latrobe Elementary). Latrobe School District receives half of all proceeds! Come join your local community and support our school!!

We are also looking for Pancake Breakfast Coordinators. This involves coordinating student volunteers to serve at the breakfasts. The Pancake Breakfasts are the last Sunday of each month. You do not need to commit to the full year. We are looking for multiple coordinators to sign up for three month stretches. Last year we raised nearly $2,000 for our school from this important fundraiser.

For 8th graders looking for community services hours, volunteer to serve at the next breakfasts:
August 27th
September 24th

Exciting news! Our Pizza Fridays start this week at Latrobe and the kids absolutely look forward to it every week!

Right now, we are in desperate need of some help passing out the pizza to the kids and are currently working on a sign-up sheet for Fridays through the New Year. It's an easy job, runs from about 11-11:30am, and the kids love to see their family passing out the pizza! Even if you can only do one Friday, it's greatly appreciated, so please contact Megan Hildebrandt at meganh8675309@yahoo.com to get your name on the list! :)

post_text:
DID YOU KNOW?

When parents are involved in their children‚Äôs education and school, those children are more likely to:

-Earn better grades.
-Score higher on tests.
-Attend school regularly.
-Have better social skills.
-Show improved behavior.
-Be more positive in their attitude toward school.
-Complete homework assignments.
-Graduate and continue their education.

Parents are more likely to:

-Be more confident at school.
-Be more confident in themselves as parents and in their abilities to help their children learn.
-Be held in higher esteem by teachers.
-Continue their own education.

Schools are more likely to have:

-Better morale among teachers.
-Higher ratings of teachers by parents.
-More support from families.
-A better reputation in the community.

The benefits of parental involvement in their children's school and education are endless and we highly encourage you to get involved in any way you can! We would love for you to join us right after drop off for Morning Stretch! It‚Äôs a great way to start the day on a positive note for students, staff, AND parents ‚ò∫

The PTC is looking to fill two open slots. We are missing a Vice President and Secretary. Our role is to raise money for our school and to have some fun along the way.

We are also looking for fill Room Parent slots for TK/K, 5th Grade and 8th Grade currently. In addition we are looking for a coordinator for the Pancake Breakfasts that happen on the last Sunday of each month.

There are a lot of great ways to get involved with the school and we strive to be as flexible as possible, knowing we all have busy schedules.

Come join us!

Remember to come out today for the Latrobe Spring Festival and Chili Palooza from 4PM-7PM at Latrobe Elementary! The weather will be fabulous and we have a lot of great chili entries.

There is Shuttle Parking available from Thompson's Toyota. If the Latrobe lot if full, go on up to Miller's Hill and park there. Meet the Shuttle on the sidewalk in front of the Latrobe Office.

There are some amazing items available for the Silent Auction including gift baskets made by each grade, a handmade quilt, garden stepping stones made by each class, an ice cream date with Mrs. Miller and much more!!!

Winners of the School Raffle will also be announced.

Lots of fun events:
Potato Sack Race
Three-Legged Race
Egg/Spoon Race
Face Painting

Chili & Cornbread
Hot Dogs
Chips
Ice Cream
Beer/Wine at the Saloon

Come join us and support our school!!!

Don't forgot to color your chili bean!!! All ages welcome to enter the coloring contest for the Chili Palooza event this Saturday, April 29th from 4-7 at Latrobe.

First place winners receive a $5 gift card to Urban Yogurt!

All ages welcome!

Flyers went home with students that had the Chili Bean coloring page attached.

Either drop your finished artwork off at the Latrobe office by Friday, April 28th, or bring it to the event and hand it in. Judging will take place during the event and winners will be announced based on grade/age categories.

Last chance to enter your best chili recipe in the Latrobe Spring Festival and Chili Palooza is on Wednesday, April 26th!!!!

The Festival is on Saturday, April 29th from 4-7. This is our biggest fundraiser of the year supporting technology for our school, and we would love to see everyone come out and support our wonderful school and taste some unique chili recipes.

We have an esteemed panel of judges that include the owners of Aji/Milesone, a master BBQer, and a food/wine pairing caterer that works with wineries in Napa.

Contact holly.wright@autodesk.com letting us know if you have a chili to enter so we can ensure we have a space for your chili. Details went home with students, but please reach out with questions.

Reminder: Pancake Breakfast this Sunday from 8-11 AM at the Odd Fellows Lodge Hall. Proceeds benefit Latrobe School!!!

We are also looking for a parent to coordinate student volunteers next year. The job involves contacting students in grades 6-8 to volunteer to serve at the breakfast once a month. If you are interested in helping with this low commitment job, please contact Mrs. Miller or a member of the PTC.

Due to student volunteers, the school receives half of the profits from each Pancake Breakfast! Please consider helping with this wonderful fundraiser. It teaches our students responsibility and brings the community together every month!

Variety Show Permission Forms have gone home with students and are due back this Friday, March 3rd. Anything Goes! Singing, Dancing, Gymnastics, Instruments, Comedy, Magic! Group or class acts are encouraged. Be creative!

Don't forget our Winter Festival on Thursday 12/15/16!
Please have all children arrive by 5:15 at Miller‚Äôs Hill. The program will start at 5:30!

Grades TK-5th will sing songs and Grades 6-8 have a video presentation they have put together with the theme ‚ÄúIf I Only Had One Wish‚Äù

We are collecting canned food at the door for local food banks to help give back to the community

There will be a winter scene photo booth set up for family portraits

We will serve cookies, hot chocolate, and water ($1 each)

There are handmade ornaments parents put together that will be on sale to raise funds for the PTC, next to the food booth. Ornaments are $4, or if you spend $5 you can get a drink/cookie/ornament package deal.
